        "post_id": "5803cc72-8c6d-4c24-b976-2b6503f48a2a",
        "user_id": 39230835,
        "body": "I not sure how the current situation works out well for China. They have real estate crash continuing. A huge misallocation of capital creating 90 million empty homes which with a falling population will never be occupied. Enough empty homes to house 3/4 of US population. Massive.  Housing and associated production represents 30% of Chinas economy. House building has dropped dramatically \n\nTo compensate for the huge destruction of wealth in building useless buildings now they are building useless cars, China currently has the capacity to make 49 million cars/light vehicles. That is roughly 50% of global demand. They have the capacity to make 800 million tonnes of steel…. 10x the USA which is an economy 30-40% larger.\n\nChina does not have markets for all this stuff just like they did not have markets for the housing. They just continue to misallocate capital. It’s a giant deck of cards",
        "status": "published",
        "parent_id": null,
