          "post_id": "5803cc72-8c6d-4c24-b976-2b6503f48a2a",
          "user_id": 58612491,
          "body": "If Trump folds too quickly, the article suggests it’s a clear win for China in the immediate “poker game.” Xi’s strategy of dragging out the conflict until U.S. confidence cracks would succeed, leaving the U.S. economically and geopolitically weaker. However, the broader fallout—global instability, awakened conflicts, or a U.S. backlash—might complicate China’s victory over time. For now, though, Xi would likely see it as a hand well played.",
